                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>any time; and may depend upon<lb/> speedy remittance as they are sold.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My time is fully occupied here<lb/> as I have the whole charge of\n                the<lb/> U. S <sic>Marshal's</sic> office together with the<lb/> Deputy clerkship in\n                the District and<lb/> Circuit Court but as the place is small<lb/> and I am\n                acquainted with every body<lb/> it will not inconvenience me in any<lb/> way to give\n                attention to any matter you<lb/> may entrust to my care; In my next<lb/> I will\n                forward names of Officers of the<lb/> Congregation.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My family are very well, and<lb/> enjoy the climate here very much.\n                My<lb/> oldest child <persName>Nellie</persName> is a pupil of <persName>Mr.<lb/>\n                    Marcuson</persName> in the Hebrew and religion<lb/> and the three occupy\n                        <persName><sic>Rachels</sic></persName> time<lb/> continually. She desires\n                to be remembered<lb/> to you. <persName>Mr. Cohen</persName> has left <placeName>St\n                    Paul</placeName><lb/> and resides in <placeName>Chicago</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Very Respy Yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">J. N. Cardoza</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37s7jc5q/canvas/p3"
